post_text:
The decision has been made to cancel the 2020 Prom that was scheduled for June 27 at Thumper Pond. The decision took into account:
- Maintaining consistency with school expectations regarding social distancing, group size meetings and overall healthy practices to protect our students and staff.
- Limitations that Thumper Pond has regarding the number of patrons allowed in the areas used for Prom & Post Prom.
- Student survey data regarding not wanting to reschedule (again) after June 27.
We understand this decision will be upsetting to some of our students and families. Please know that we made this decision in the overall best interest of our student and staff at this time.

post_text:
Details regarding the graduation program on Sunday, May 24 @ 9:15 pm at the HENNING fairgrounds:
1. The police department and fire department will begin directing parking at 9:00 pm (car size will be used to determine parking placement to attempt to reduce obstructed views). Vehicles will enter the fairgrounds from Jenson Street and will need to have their car ticket for entrance.
2. The graduation program will begin at approximately 9:15 pm and will be broadcasted on the radio channel 89.5 fm.
3. Make sure to use the bathroom prior to attending graduation. There will be no public bathrooms available due to Covid restrictions.
4. The program is approximately one hour and 15 minutes long - bring snacks 🥨
5. All guests and students (except for the three student speakers) will be required to remain in their vehicles.
6. If weather does not cooperate, the graduation ceremony will be postponed until Monday, May 25 @ 9:15 pm with the same guidelines.

The Graduating Class of 2020 will have a graduation ceremony like no other Henning High School graduating class before. The Class of 2020 will have their graduation ceremony in a Drive-in style with a blend of videos and on stage speeches. The ceremony will be held on Sunday, May 24 at 9:15 pm at the Henning fairgrounds. Due to Covid restrictions, each family is allowed only two cars at the event.
Students will be recorded receiving their diplomas individually on stage at the school either on Wednesday, May 20 or Thursday, May 21 (a schedule has been shared with each student). Each student is allowed a maximum of seven (7) family members at their individual graduation recording.
#Classof2020
#HenningStrong

post_text:
Credit KIKV 100.7 FM Alexandria Minnesota:
Trevor is an 11 year old 5th grader in Henning, MN he made a goal to donate an item a day (30 or 31 items a month) to the local food shelf in Henning. He started January 1, 2020 and to date has donated 239 lbs of food, had a Facebook birthday fundraiser for the food shelf and raised $461. He also has a local business (Our Home Your Home) matching his food donations every month. He wants to do this for the whole year. He works to earn money and he decides what to get, helps with purchasing the items and delivers them to the food shelf each month. He is an outstanding, caring boy with a BIG heart for others!!
text:
Credit KIKV 100.7 FM Alexandria Minnesota:
Trevor is an 11 year old 5th grader in Henning, MN he made a goal to donate an item a day (30 or 31 items a month) to the local food shelf in Henning. He started January 1, 2020 and to date has donated 239 lbs of food, had a Facebook birthday fundraiser for the food shelf and raised $461. He also has a local business (Our Home Your Home) matching his food donations every month. He wants to do this for the whole year. He works to earn money and he decides what to get, helps with purchasing the items and delivers them to the food shelf each month. He is an outstanding, caring boy with a BIG heart for others!!

post_text: Hey Henning School Families!!! We want to make you aware that the meals that are being delivered - are FREE to ALL our families. All children have the ability to receive a free breakfast and lunch throughout the week at no cost to your family. We just need you to communicate with us and complete the proper paperwork to be added to our delivery list. Starting Monday, March 23 we will drop off meals for multiple days at a time. Please place a cooler by your door for items to be placed in. Please try to keep pets away from our delivery personnel and understand that we will not be handing food directly to someone hand-to-hand, this is why the cooler is important. All foods are fully cooked and properly prepared. Delivery times are between 10:30-12:45. Stay STRONG Henning School Families!

post_text:
ARVIG is stepping up to help out families without internet.

This program is available to families who live in the Arvig service area and currently do not have any internet service at their residence
Any internet speed available will be offered free-of-charge, including wi-fi service if needed
To qualify for free service, they must be a new customer, have no bad debt with Arvig and sign up for paperless statements
The service will remain free until the 2019/2020 school year concludes unless they call to disconnect their service and return equipment
Unfortunately, if we are unable to deliver 5 Mbps speed to their residence, we won’t be able to offer them this program
We will prioritize service installations for low-income families. Verification of need may be provided via a conference call with the school

post_text: Good Morning Henning Public School Family – it has been announced by Govern Walz that all Minnesota Schools will be shut down from March 18th – March 27th with a return to school Monday, March 30th. I understand this creates numerous issues for our families; rest assured our team is working on plans to continue to meet the needs of our students during the shutdown. I know there are several questions at this time; as soon as I learn more information I will be sure to communicate with our school family. This will be a very challenging situation for all of us, but we are fortunate to have an amazing staff, students, and communities – we will get through this!

Effectively Immediately Friday, March 13, 2020 10:45 a.m.

The Minnesota State High School League is immediately cancelling the Girls Basketball State Tournament.

Additionally, all Boys Section and State Basketball Tournaments have been cancelled.

Section Speech Tournament events for the week of March 15-21 have been postponed indefinitely.

Additional details and information on other upcoming events including Spring Activities will be shared later today.

post_text:
**Notice** Statement on Minnesota State High School League Postseason Tournament
and COVID-19:
The Minnesota State High School League, relying on information from the Minnesota
Department of Health, will limit the number of people at tournaments beginning Friday,
March 13, 2020. This decision will impact Girls Basketball Semifinals and Finals, the
Adapted Floor Hockey Tournament, and Section Boys Basketball games. As the
COVID-19 situation is rapidly evolving, plans for events held after this weekend are still being developed and will be communicated at a later date.

Because of the short notice Henning Public School will remain closed tomorrow 3/12/20.

Full Press Release is available here: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1s_7TKREHFTrxxTOno6cXppEhGH8HLzr-/view?usp=sharing
